My Meme

The meme I have created is to express how students may feel during the semester, this is where my motivation and originality came from making it a meme and formating it the way I did gives it comedic value.

My Meme

library(magick)

#The first image in the meme
happy_sem_start <- image_read("https://i1.sndcdn.com/artworks-JeZQh6Hbil2Er51B-U9rx3A-t500x500.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(600)

#This section of code is for the text that will appear next to the meme

semstart_text <- image_blank(width = 600, 
                        height = 600, 
                        color = "#171616") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Begining\nof\nSemester",
                 color = "#eb34c6",
                 size = 60,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

#The second image in the meme
depressed_sem_end <- image_read("https://i1.sndcdn.com/artworks-dcZZznwvCIjxzVdh-Ia2kPw-t500x500.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(600)

#This section of code is also for the text that will appear next to the meme

semend_text <- image_blank(width = 600, 
                       height = 600, 
                       color = "#171616") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "End\nof\nSemester",
                 color = "#eb34c6",
                 size = 60,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

#This code is to stitch together all the images and code and create the final meme

first_row <- image_append(c(happy_sem_start, semstart_text)) 

second_row <- image_append(c(depressed_sem_end, semend_text))


meme <- c(first_row, second_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE) %>%
  image_scale
(800)
image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")

My Gif

The inspiration and originality of my gif came from my meme, I wanted to use a similar format but on a larger time scale to create the same comedic relief my meme has.

My Gif

library(magick)
#here are the four different images for my gif 

first_year <- image_read("https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/the-uncanny-incredible/images/5/5f/Mibu_phase_1_%28original_hd%29.webp/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/1000?cb=20220507214041") %>%
  image_scale(500)

second_year <- image_read("https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/the-uncanny-incredible/images/e/e7/Phase_2_HD.jpg/revision/latest?cb=20220216163526") %>%
  image_scale(500)

third_year <- image_read("https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/the-uncanny-incredible/images/8/8c/Traumatized_Remake.webp/revision/latest?cb=20220216081741") %>%
  image_scale(500)

post_grad <- image_read("https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/the-uncanny-incredible/images/a/ad/7hd.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/350?cb=20220809223158") %>%
  image_scale(500)

#The coding here will be the annotation that goes with the images
frame1 <- first_year %>%
  image_annotate(text = "First\nYear", size = 50, gravity = "North",
                 font = "Impact",color = "#0073FF") %>%
  image_scale(500) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

frame2 <- second_year %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Second\nYear", size = 50, gravity = "North",
                 font = "Impact",color = "#0073FF") %>%
  image_scale(500) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

frame3 <- third_year %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Third\nYear", size = 50, gravity = "North",
                 font = "Impact",color = "#0073FF") %>%
  image_scale(500) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

frame4 <- post_grad %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Post\nGrad", size = 50, gravity = "North",
                 font = "Impact",color = "#0073FF") %>%
  image_scale(500) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

#This code stitches all the frames together and makes the animated gif work as a gif
frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4)

#Ive set the fps to 1 as slow as possible to ensure that all images can ve viewed 

animation <- image_animate(frames, fps = 1)

image_write(animation, "my_animation.gif")
